ACT:
 Indian Penal Code, 1860: ss. 302 & 201--Conviction based on circumstantial evidence--Facts consistent with innocence of accused-Whether entitled to benefit of doubt--Tendency of free fabrication of record to implicate innocents in capital offence deprecated.
 Constitution of India: Articles 14, 19, 21 & 39A/Univer- sal Declaration of Human Rights: Articles 3 & 10--Indigent accused--Right to liberty and life, equal justice and free legal aid--Need to assign experienced amicus curiae to ensure effective and meaningful defence emphasised.
 
